    "body": "We should create subclasses of `PerlPackage` for common Perl build systems.\r\n\r\n### Rationale\r\n\r\nThe current `PerlPackage` is rather complex and difficult to extend. It would be better structured with subclasses.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nHere are some common Perl build systems I've found:\r\n\r\n| Build Tool | Filename |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| [`Module::Build`](https://metacpan.org/pod/Module::Build) | `Build.PL` |\r\n| [`Module::Install`](https://metacpan.org/pod/Module::Install) | `Makefile.PL` |\r\n| [`ExtUtils::MakeMaker`](https://metacpan.org/pod/ExtUtils::MakeMaker) | `Makefile.PL` |\r\n| [`Dist::Zilla`](https://metacpan.org/pod/Dist::Zilla) | `Dist.Ini` |\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\nhttp://preaction.me/talks/Perl/Compare-Building-Modules.html\r\n\r\nWe may want to consider something similar for `PythonPackage` since there are multiple Python build systems (Distutils, Setuptools, Poetry, etc.)",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
